He's creating a golem for an amazing reason.

I was thinking about how one of the few good aspects of the modern regime of LGBT rights, open homosexuality being publicly acceptable, etc. in the West is that you do not have to worry about one of your friends secretly being a homosexual. Used to be a doubt/concern in the past.

If you read some historical stuff men would occasionally be suspicious of some associate being homosexual in secret, there would be rumors going around that you could never be sure about, you would try to convince yourself he is a stand-up guy, no way, etc. Nowadays not a concern

Insomniacs give a bad name to the sounds of the night because they blame them for their own wakefulness. Clocks ticking, washing machine running, cars outside idling and late night birds singing by the window, etc. are all very pleasant if you're not anxious about falling asleep.

Small sins are often more pernicious than big ones we are wary of. The ship that inspired Moby Dick had been damaged by shipworms before it was sunk by a whale. "When there is respect for small things, there will be an even greater respect towards the bigger things." St. Paisios.
Okay this was mostly an excuse to post the Moby Dick factoid. I read it on the shipworm Wikipedia page.
